# 014-move-playability-improvements

There a number of playability issues that need to be improved before the playtest.

## Clearly visualize a move played and move freeze until next round

As soon as the first player makes their move, they should be prevented to make further moves until the next round, i.e. until the opponent hase made their move, which triggers next round.

Make the move visually clear on the board to the first player. Second player only sees the first player's timer stop, not which move was made.

The tiles moved should not be moved back to their original location as is done now. The move should be visible on screen as orange tiles until next round.

## Visualize opponents move on round completion

The move made by an opponent should be shown briefly as orange with a fade out to correct color at round completion. I.e. the player should be shown visually on the board the move made by their opponent on round comletion.

## More prominent timer and timer pause color

The timer of both players should be prominent on the screen, e.g. as a panel/tile with colored background indicating status, green when ticking, orange when paused, red when zero/time-out. As soon as move is made the timer is paused until next round and should be orange, and clearly visible to both players.

## Timer out of both players should trigger game end

When both players' timer goes to zero in mid round, the game should stop with indication of a timeout. Then the game should be completed immediately and go directly to the game summary screen.

## Show all tiles colored at final game summary screen

Currently, the final-summary-screen shows the board grid without tile-freeze color, i.e. you don't see which tiles were scored. The summary screen should show the tile colors so that it is visible to the players who owned which tiles.

## Show tiny tile score value on tiles (as in Scrabble tiles)

The value of each tile, i.e. the character value, should be visible as a tiny number on the tile bottom right, à la Scrabble tiles.

## The round summary table should be visible to the right in first round

Currently the round summary table is not shown at the beginning of a game in the first round but then suddenly appears at the end of the round and reshapes the whole screen which is discracting and confusing to players. For the MVP the table should be simply shown from the beginning, although it will be empty in the first round.
